1. Add a Smooth Scroll and Navigation

Currently, users have to scroll manually. Adding a sticky navbar with links to sections improves usability:

  </nav>
</header>

And add id attributes to your sections:

html
<section id="about">...</section>
<section id="achievements">...</section>
<section id="projects">...</section>
<section id="resume">...</section>
<section id="contact">...</section>

2. Modern Card Hover Effect

Add subtle animation to make the cards interactive:

css
.card {
  background: white;
  padding: 20px;
  margin: 15px 0;
  border-radius: 10px;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  transition: transform 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
}

.card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-5px);
  box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
}

3. Resume Button Styling

Make it stand out more with a hover effect:

css
.resume-btn:hover {
  background: #2563eb;

}

4. Add a Hero Image or Background Gradient

To make the header pop:

css

  background: linear-gradient(to right, #1e3a8a, #2563eb);
  color: white;
  text-align: center;

5. Optional: Add Font Awesome Icons

For projects, achievements, and contact links to look more visually appealing:

bash

├─ index.html       ← Your complete portfolio HTML
├─ resume.pdf       ← Your resume file
├─ assets/          ← Optional folder for images/icons (empty for now)
└─ README.md        ← Optional info about your portfolio

Step 2: resume.pdf

  • Place your actual resume in the same folder and name it exactly: resume.pdf.

Step 3: Optional assets folder

  • For images or icons, create assets/ inside the folder.

  • You can add future images like this: <img src="assets/photo.jpg" alt="Photo">.

Step 4: Optional README.md

markdown
# Sumeet Pandey Portfolio
This is the personal portfolio website of Sumeet Pandey.  
Built using HTML & CSS.  
Hosted on GitHub Pages.

✅ Now you’re ready to upload

  1. Go to GitHub → New Repository → Name it portfolio.

  2. Upload all files and folders from PortfolioWebsite/.

  3. Enable GitHub Pages → Source: main → /root.

  4. Your site will be live at:

arduino
https://<your-username>.github.io/portfolio/
